Here are the user stories for the provided Python code:

As a Data Administrator, I want to process deletions for a specific date, so that data remains clean and up-to-date.  
As a UI Designer, I want to redesign the Resources page, so that it matches new Broker styles.  
As a UI Designer, I want to report user testing results to agencies, so that they can review feedback.  
As a DevOps Engineer, I want to configure New Relic for all applications, so that we can monitor performance and errors.  
As a Broker User, I want to sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load, so that files are generated only when data is updated.  
As a Broker User, I want to update SQL codes for clarity, so that queries are easier to maintain.  
As a Broker User, I want to improve PPoPCode derivation logic, so that it includes special cases like 00***** and 00FORGN.  
As a Broker User, I want to derive FundingAgencyCode, so that data quality is improved.  
As a Broker User, I want to map FederalActionObligation to Atom Feed, so that financial data is accurately reflected.  
As a Broker User, I want to validate PPoP ZIP codes, so that they match Legal Entity ZIP entries.  
As a UI Designer, I want to edit landing pages (DABS/FABS/Homepage/Help), so that content remains current.  
As a UI Designer, I want to schedule user testing with advanced notice, so that participants are prepared.  
As a UI Designer, I want to track Tech Thursday issues, so that they can be addressed in testing.  
As a UI Designer, I want to create a summary of UI testing results, so that improvements can be documented.  
As a Developer, I want to enhance logging for troubleshooting, so that issues are easier to diagnose.  
As a Developer, I want to ensure only grant records are sent to USAspending, so that data integrity is maintained.  
As a Developer, I want to update the header info box with date and time, so that users see accurate timestamps.  
As a Website User, I want to access published FABS files, so that I can review the latest data.  
As a Developer, I want to update FABS submission status when publishStatus changes, so that records stay synchronized.  
As a Developer, I want to add GTAS window data to the database, so that financial tracking is complete.  
As a Developer, I want to update the FABS sample file, so that outdated fields like FundingAgencyCode are removed.  
As a Developer, I want to deactivate the publish button during derivations, so that users don’t submit incomplete data.  
As a Developer, I want to load historical FABS data with derived fields, so that past records are consistent.  
As a FABS User, I want to get accurate frontend URLs for pages, so that navigation is seamless.  
As a FABS User, I want to get additional helpful info for the submission dashboard, so that I can track progress.  
As a Broker User, I want to update error message text for accuracy, so that users receive clear feedback.  
As a Broker User, I want to update validation rules, so that they align with latest requirements.  
As a User, I want to validate DUNS based on ActionType and dates, so that records meet compliance standards.  
As a Developer, I want to cache D Files generation requests, so that duplicate processing is avoided.  
As a Developer, I want to prevent double publishing of FABS submissions, so that data isn’t duplicated.  
As an Agency User, I want to handle large numbers of flexfields efficiently, so that performance isn’t impacted.  
As an Agency User, I want to validate FABS records for zero/blank values, so that loan data is accurate.  
As an Agency User, I want to ensure SAM data is complete, so that records are reliable.  
As a Data User, I want to get daily updates for FABS records, so that I stay informed.  
As a Developer, I want to derive office names from office codes, so that displays are user-friendly.  
As a Developer, I want to update the SAMPLE FILE link in the dialog, so that users access the correct resource.  
As a Developer, I want to handle partial ZIP codes, so that validation is flexible.  
As a Developer, I want to update status labels on the Submission Dashboard, so that progress is clearly indicated.

# Configure logging
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)

class DataDeletion:
    """Handles data deletion for a specific date."""
    
    def delete_for_date(self, target_date: datetime.date) -> bool:

        logger.info(f"Processing deletions for date: {target_date}")
        # Implementation would interact with the database
        return True  # Assuming deletion was successful

class UIDesigner:
    """Handles UI-related tasks."""
    
    def redesign_resources_page(self, new_style: Dict) -> bool:
        """Redesign Resources page to match new styles."""
        logger.info(f"Redesigning Resources page with new styles: {new_style}")
        return True
    
    def report_user_testing(self, results: Dict, agencies: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Report user testing results to specified agencies."""
        logger.info(f"Reporting user testing results to agencies: {agencies}")
        return True

class DevOpsEngineer:
    """Handles DevOps configurations."""
    
    def configure_new_relic(self, app_names: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Configure New Relic for all specified applications."""
        logger.info(f"Configuring New Relic for apps: {app_names}")
        return True

class BrokerUser:
    """Handles broker-related functionalities."""
    
    def sync_d1_with_fpds(self) -> bool:
        """Sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load."""
        logger.info("Syncing D1 file generation with FPDS data load")
        return True
    
    def update_sql_codes(self, sql_scripts: Dict[str, str]) -> bool:
        """Update SQL codes for clarity and maintainability."""
        for script_name, script in sql_scripts.items():
            logger.info(f"Updating SQL script: {script_name}")
        return True
    
    def improve_ppop_code_logic(self, special_cases: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Improve PPoPCode derivation logic to include special cases."""
        logger.info(f"Updating PPoPCode logic with special cases: {special_cases}")
        return True
    
    def derive_funding_agency_code(self) -> bool:
        """Derive FundingAgencyCode to improve data quality."""
        logger.info("Deriving FundingAgencyCode")
        return True
    
    def map_federal_action_to_atom_feed(self) -> bool:
        """Map FederalActionObligation to Atom Feed."""
        logger.info("Mapping FederalActionObligation to Atom Feed")
        return True
    
    def validate_ppop_zip_codes(self) -> bool:
        """Validate PPoP ZIP codes against Legal Entity ZIP entries."""
        logger.info("Validating PPoP ZIP codes")
        return True

class WebsiteUser:
    """Handles website-related functionalities."""
    
    def get_published_fabs_files(self) -> List[str]:
        """Retrieve published FABS files."""
        logger.info("Fetching published FABS files")
        return ["file1.csv", "file2.csv"]  # Example file list

class Developer:
    """Handles developer-related tasks."""
    
    def enhance_logging(self) -> bool:
        """Enhance logging for better troubleshooting."""
        logger.info("Enhancing logging configuration")
        return True
    
    def ensure_grant_records_to_usaspending(self) -> bool:
        """Ensure only grant records are sent to USAspending."""
        logger.info("Filtering records for USAspending")
        return True
    
    def update_header_info_box(self) -> bool:
        """Update header info box with current date and time."""
        now = datetime.datetime.now(pytz.utc)
        logger.info(f"Updating header with timestamp: {now}")
        return True
    
    def update_fabs_submission_status(self, submission_id: str, new_status: str) -> bool:
        """Update FABS submission status when publishStatus changes."""
        logger.info(f"Updating FABS submission {submission_id} to status: {new_status}")
        return True
    
    def add_gtas_window_data(self, data: Dict) -> bool:
        """Add GTAS window data to the database."""
        logger.info("Adding GTAS window data to the database")
        return True
    
    def update_fabs_sample_file(self) -> bool:
        """Update FABS sample file by removing outdated fields."""
        logger.info("Updating FABS sample file")
        return True
    
    def toggle_publish_button(self, active: bool) -> bool:
        """Toggle the publish button during derivations."""
        status = "active" if active else "disabled"
        logger.info(f"Setting publish button to: {status}")
        return True
    
    def load_historical_fabs_data(self) -> bool:
        """Load historical FABS data with derived fields."""
        logger.info("Loading historical FABS data")
        return True
    
    def get_frontend_urls(self, page_names: List[str]) -> Dict[str, str]:
        """Get accurate frontend URLs for specified pages."""
        urls = {name: f"https://example.com/{name.lower()}" for name in page_names}
        logger.info(f"Generated frontend URLs: {urls}")
        return urls
    
    def update_error_messages(self, updates: Dict[str, str]) -> bool:
        """Update error message text for accuracy."""
        for old_msg, new_msg in updates.items():
            logger.info(f"Updating error message: '{old_msg}' -> '{new_msg}'")
        return True
    
    def cache_d_files_requests(self) -> bool:
        """Cache D Files generation requests to avoid duplicates."""
        logger.info("Caching D Files generation requests")
        return True
    
    def prevent_double_publishing(self, submission_id: str) -> bool:
        """Prevent double publishing of FABS submissions."""
        logger.info(f"Preventing double publishing for submission: {submission_id}")
        return True
    
    def derive_office_names(self, office_codes: List[str]) -> Dict[str, str]:
        """Derive office names from office codes."""
        office_names = {code: f"Office-{code}" for code in office_codes}
        logger.info(f"Derived office names: {office_names}")
        return office_names
    
    def handle_partial_zip_codes(self, zip_codes: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Handle partial ZIP codes during validation."""
        logger.info(f"Processing partial ZIP codes: {zip_codes}")
        return True

class FABSUser:
    """Handles FABS-related functionalities."""
    
    def get_submission_dashboard_info(self) -> Dict:
        """Get additional helpful info for the submission dashboard."""
        info = {
            "last_updated": datetime.datetime.now(pytz.utc),
            "status": "processing",
            "progress": 75
        }
        logger.info("Fetching submission dashboard info")
        return info

@dataclass
class UIValidationRules:
    """Stores UI validation rules."""
    rules: Dict[str, str]

    def update_rules(self, new_rules: Dict[str, str]) -> None:
        """Update validation rules."""
        self.rules.update(new_rules)
        logger.info(f"Updated validation rules: {self.rules}")

class DataUser:
    """Handles data-related tasks."""
    
    def get_daily_fabs_updates(self) -> List[Dict]:
        """Get daily updates for FABS records."""
        updates = [{"id": "1", "status": "updated"}, {"id": "2", "status": "new"}]
        logger.info("Fetching daily FABS updates")
        return updates

class UserTestingScheduler:
    """Manages user testing scheduling."""
    
    def schedule_testing(self, participants: List[str], test_date: datetime.date) -> bool:
        """Schedule user testing with advanced notice."""
        logger.info(f"Scheduling user testing on {test_date} for participants: {participants}")
        return True

class TechThursdayTracker:
    """Tracks Tech Thursday issues."""
    
    def track_issues(self, issues: List[str]) -> bool:
        """Track issues for Tech Thursday."""
        logger.info(f"Tracking Tech Thursday issues: {issues}")
        return True

class UITestingSummary:
    """Creates summaries of UI testing results."""
    
    def create_summary(self, results: Dict) -> str:
        """Create a summary of UI testing results."""
        summary = f"Testing Summary: {len(results)} tests completed."
        logger.info(summary)
        return summary

    ui_designer.redesign_resources_page({"color": "blue", "font": "Arial"})
    
    dev_ops = DevOpsEngineer()
